        "id": "docling_magazine_TheEconomist.2024.03.02_page_032_91",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "\"I'm rooting the BJP to the ground here.\"",
        "bbox": [
          0.6564885567834758,
          0.06820436523360322,
          0.9217557212699592,
          0.0828488371325148
        ],
        "order": 4
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_magazine_TheEconomist.2024.03.02_page_032_93",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "And to build the party's presence in the state, he says he is putting \"growth, growth and growth\" at the centre of its campaign. \"I don't think we need to respond to ideology with ideology,\" he adds. In particular, the jp has to tread carefully on the idea of making Hindi a national language, as it has sometimes advocated. That issue has often provoked protests in the south, including deadly riots in Tamil Nadu in 1965.",
        "bbox": [
          0.6583969430282893,
          0.08283730135577556,
          0.9408396913151019,
          0.2136627906801168
        ],
        "order": 7
      }
    ]
  },
