      {
        "id": "docling_magazine_TheEconomist.2024.03.02_page_032_92",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "When Mr Modi addressed the rally on February 27th, he avoided that subject but spoke of his love for local language and culture, recalling that he had quoted from a 6th century Bc Tamil poem at the UN. He also avoided mentioning his inauguration of a controversial Hindu temple in northern India, despite its centrality to his campaign elsewhere. While outlining his government's support for Tamil Nadu, he praised the state's entrepreneurial spirit. (He mostly spoke in Hindi, however.)",
